# Walkthrough — Exposing Master CV to All Users

The Master CV Builder module has been updated to be fully accessible to all registered users (including free tier accounts) rather than being restricted only to users with `is_agent_buyer` active.

## Changes Made

### 1. Database Module
#### [MODIFY] [database.py](file:///c:/Users/VIBUDH/Desktop/projects/job%20assistant/core/database.py)
* Added `import json` globally at the top level of `database.py` to fix a potential runtime `NameError` in `get_master_cv` and `save_master_cv`.

### 2. Backend Routing
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/VIBUDH/Desktop/projects/job%20assistant/core/app.py)
Removed the `is_agent_buyer` check from all five Master CV-related endpoints:
* **GET `/api/user/master-cv`** (Retrieves Master CV JSON template/content)
* **POST `/api/user/master-cv`** (Saves Master CV JSON data)
* **POST `/api/user/master-cv/parse-resume`** (Parses PDF/DOCX to JSON via Claude)
* **POST `/api/user/master-cv/generate-headline`** (Generates career summary via Claude)
* **POST `/api/user/master-cv/generate-tailored`** (Generates target tailored PDF)

### 3. Frontend Dashboard
#### [MODIFY] [dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/VIBUDH/Desktop/projects/job%20assistant/frontend/dashboard.html)
* **Sidebar Tab Visibility**: Modified `renderSidebar()` so the `#cvNavLink` (Master CV tab) is always rendered and never hidden based on user subscription level.
* **Navigation Router**: Removed the redirection check in the hash router that previously sent non-paying users visiting `#cv` back to the `#store` page.

